The paper deals with program synthesis, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of a neural network to guide search suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with constructing correct programs, which is a software engineering concern (cs.SE). The use of Linear Temporal Logic (LTL) suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with synthesizing strategies for potentially adversarial environments, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY).
